main event: An unidentified circular track was observed on December 29, 1959, on Southern Victoria Island, Canada.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 25 minutes, The object was tracked using ground-radar, The object exhibited an erratic course with a speed range of 40 to 50 knots, There was speculation that the object could possibly be a balloon, The report indicates possible anomalous propagation and temperature inversion affecting radar readings.
